The Scale Natural Language Tasks Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement natural language tasks. The parameters attachment_type, attachment, and taxonomies will be stored in the params object of the constructed task object.

The Scale Natural Language Tasks Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement natural language tasks that include spam detection, copyright detection, and product categorization. If successful, Scale will immediately return the generated task object.

The Scale Natural Language Tasks JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to integrate natural language features. This task involves a markdown-enabled instruction about how to make the categorization, an attachment of what to categorize, an attachment_type, and taxonomies.

The Scale Natural Language Tasks Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement a natural language task. The endpoint creates a categorization task. In this task, one of the workers at Scale will view the attachment and select the correct answer for every taxonomy and every question.

The Scale Polygon Annotation Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to implement a polygon annotation feature. The code includes a callback URL, an instruction to draw a polygon around an image, an attachment, and objects to annotate.

The Scale Polygon Annotation Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement a polygon annotation. The required parameters for this task are callback_url, attachment, and objects_to_annotate. The callback_url is the URL that will be POSTed on task completion.

The Scale Polygon Annotation JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to create a polygon annotation task. It includes a callback URL, an instruction (example: draw a polygon around every car in the image), an attachment, and objects to annotate.

The Scale Polygon Annotation Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement polygon annotations. The endpoint creates a polygon annotation task. In this task, one of the labelers at Scale will view the given image and draw bounding polygons around the specified objects, returning the vertices of these polygons.

The Scale Computer Vision Tasks Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement computer vision tasks. The required parameters for this task are callback_url, attachment, and objects_to_annotate. The callback_url is the URL that will be POSTed on task completion and is described in more detail in the callbacks section.

The Scale Computer Vision Tasks Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement computer vision tasks. Each annotation will be annotated with a label specifying what type of object it is, with the label coming from the provided objects_to_annotate list.

The Scale Computer Vision Tasks JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how developers can implement computer vision tasks. The required parameters for this task are callback_url, attachment, and objects_to_annotate. The callback_url is the URL that will be POSTed on task completion.

The Scale Computer Vision Tasks Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to create an annotation task. In this task, one of the labelers at Scale will view the given image and draw bounding boxes around the specified objects, returning the positions and sizes of these boxes.

The Scale Sentiment and Intent Analysis Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to implement sentiment and intent analysis. As an endpoint, it creates a categorization task in which one of the workers will view the attachment and select the correct answer for every taxonomy/question. Example use cases are spam detection, copyright detection, and product categorization.

The Scale Task Object Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement categorization, transcription, audio transcription, comparison, annotation, and data collection tasks. Objects include attributes, metadata, and attachments.

The Scale Task Object Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement a task object. Scale supports categorization, transcription, audio transcription, comparison, annotation, and data collection.

The Scale Task Object JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement a task object. The task object represents a single task that a developer creates with Scale and is completed by a worker.
The Scale Task Object Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to implement a task object that represents a single task that a developer creates with Scale and is completed by a worker.

The Scale Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate the API. Developers can replace a Scale API Key with the developer's API Key. When logging in, the API key will be automatically filled in the docs.

The Scale Python Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate the API. Developers can use an API Key included in all API requests to the server via HTTP Basic Auth. Developers can provide the API Key as the basic auth username value without a password.

The Scale JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to use an API Key to authenticate the client. Developers can replace the Scale API Key with a personal Key. When developers log in, the key will be automatically filled in the docs.
The Scale Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate the API. With curl, developers can just pass the correct header with each request. They can use an API Key to validate.
